{"type":"message","id":"15cfb70f","parentId":"5f9fe100","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:55:36.478Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ahkrwgyms4b6_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 155513\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state from the provided context:\r\n\r\n1. **Last pulse**: pulse_2026-03-24 155352.md\r\n2. **Current work**: CFI Compression Experiment - completed, found that:\r\n   - CFI alone loses 92.9% recall\r\n   - Constant format tokens (freq=160, CFI=1.00) are metaprogramming artifacts with zero information\r\n   - Need THREE-DIMENSIONAL filter: CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120)\r\n   - Next experiment: Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring\r\n\r\n3. **Pending action**: Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\r\n   - Formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n   - Test if this distinguishes \"constant format\" from \"research trajectory\"\r\n   - Run: 200 pulses, 80/20 split, compare against binary thresholds\r\n\r\n4. **Key insight**: The next concrete action is to run the hybrid scoring experiment.\r\n\r\nSince this is a research/pulse context, I need to:\r\n1. First, check/create the state file with the experiment design\r\n2. Run the actual experiment comparing the hybrid formula against binary thresholds\r\n\r\nLooking at the pending actions, the most concrete next step is to implement and run the Hybrid CFI×Freq^0.5 scoring experiment. I should:\r\n\r\n1. Create/update the experiment spec for the hybrid scoring approach\r\n2. This would involve updating `research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md` or creating a new experiment file\r\n\r\nLet me create the experiment design document that will enable running this comparison experiment. The experiment needs to:\r\n- Take 200 pulses\r\n- Split 80/20 for training/test\r\n- Compare score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120) against binary thresholds\r\n\r\n\r\n- Evaluate precision and recall\r\n\r\nI'll develop a script to process pulse data and generate comparative metrics. The key will be implementing a flexible scoring mechanism that captures the nuanced relationship between CFI and frequency. This involves creating functions to calculate scores, apply hybrid and binary filtering, and generate detailed performance analysis across different token categories.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI compression synthesis identified that constant-format tokens (freq=160, CFI=1.0) are metaprogramming noise, while the hybrid formula score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120) could distinguish these from true research trajectory tokens. The next concrete action is to implement and run this experiment.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the hybrid scoring experiment implementation that will test whether score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120) outperforms binary CFI/freq thresholds at separating signal from noise across 200 pulses.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI×Freq Hybrid Scoring Experiment\r\n## Strategy C: Continuous Score vs Binary Thresholds\r\n**Created:** 2026-03-24\r\n**Status:** PENDING\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nThe formula `score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)` will:\r\n1. Deweight constant-format tokens (freq≈160 → min(1,160/120)=1 → score=CFI×1, BUT CFI≈1 means still problematic)\r\n2. Boost research trajectory tokens (freq<120 → freq/120 < 1, multiplied by CFI≥0.5)\r\n3. Suppress noise tokens (low CFI) regardless of frequency\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n- **Pulses:** 200 (160 train / 40 test)\r\n- **Baseline:** Binary thresholds (CFI≥0.5 AND freq∈[3,120))\r\n- **Test:** Hybrid score(T) with various cutoff thresholds\r\n- **Metrics:** Precision, Recall, F1 per token category (constant-format, research-trajectory, noise)\r\n\r\n## Expected Outcome\r\nIf hypothesis holds, hybrid scoring should achieve higher F1 than binary thresholds by:\r\n- Capturing more research trajectory tokens (higher recall)\r\n- Still rejecting constant-format tokens (precision maintained)\r\n\r\n## Implementation\r\nSee: `src/hybrid_scoring_experiment.ps1`\r\nfile: research/HYBRID_SCORING_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 15:55:30\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774382136477}}
